column2: 2028 Energy Code: Nonresidential Greenhouse Gas Electricity Emissions Hourly Factors

column4: 12/18/25 - SAC - created NRes table from Nonres Elec tab of:  2028_Energy_Code_Greenhouse_Gas_Emissions_Hourly_Factors_ada.xlsx

column2: These hourly factors are used to convert predicted site energy use to long run marginal greenhouse gas emissions.
These hourly factors must be used with a computer program approved for demonstrating compliance with the 2028 Energy Code by the California Energy Commission.
These hourly factors are formatted to the 2009 calendar year, where January 3rd & 4th are the first weekend of the year.
These hourly factors assume a 30-year period of analysis.
